{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Does anybody know when the stethoscope was invented?"},{"time":5000,"text":"Any guesses? 1816."},{"time":8000,"text":"And what I can say is, in 2016,"},{"time":11000,"text":"doctors aren't going to be walking around with stethoscopes."},{"time":13000,"text":"There's a whole lot better technology coming,"},{"time":15000,"text":"and that's part of the change in medicine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18000,"text":"What has changed our society"},{"time":21000,"text":"has been wireless devices."},{"time":23000,"text":"But the future are digital medical wireless devices, OK?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":28000,"text":"So, let me give you some examples of this"},{"time":30000,"text":"to kind of make this much more concrete."},{"time":33000,"text":"This is the first one. This is an electrocardiogram."},{"time":36000,"text":"And, as a cardiologist, to think that you could see in real time"},{"time":39000,"text":"a patient, an individual, anywhere in the world"},{"time":42000,"text":"on your smartphone,"},{"time":44000,"text":"watching your rhythm -- that's incredible,"},{"time":46000,"text":"and it's with us today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48000,"text":"But that's just the beginning."},{"time":51000,"text":"You check your email while you're sitting here."},{"time":54000,"text":"In the future you're going to be checking all your vital signs,"},{"time":58000,"text":"all your vital signs: your heart rhythm,"},{"time":60000,"text":"your blood pressure, your oxygen, your temperature, etc."},{"time":64000,"text":"This is already available today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66000,"text":"This is AirStrip Technologies."},{"time":68000,"text":"It's now wired -- or I should say, wireless --"},{"time":72000,"text":"by taking the aggregate of these signals"},{"time":74000,"text":"in the hospital, in the intensive care unit,"},{"time":76000,"text":"and putting it on a smartphone for physicians."},{"time":79000,"text":"If you're an expectant parent,"},{"time":81000,"text":"what about the ability to monitor, continuously,"},{"time":84000,"text":"fetal heart rate, or intrauterine contractions,"},{"time":87000,"text":"and not having to worry so much that things are"},{"time":90000,"text":"fine as the pregnancy,"},{"time":92000,"text":"and moving over into the time of delivery?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":95000,"text":"And then as we go further,"},{"time":98000,"text":"today we have continuous glucose sensors."},{"time":100000,"text":"Right now, they are under the skin,"},{"time":102000,"text":"but in the future, they won't have to be implanted."},{"time":106000,"text":"And of course, the desired range -- trying to keep glucose"},{"time":108000,"text":"between 75 and less than 200,"},{"time":112000,"text":"checking it every five minutes in a continuous glucose sensor --"},{"time":115000,"text":"you'll see how that can impact diabetes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117000,"text":"And what about sleep?"},{"time":119000,"text":"We're going to zoom in on that a little bit."},{"time":121000,"text":"We're supposed to spend a third of our life in sleep."},{"time":123000,"text":"What if, on your phone,"},{"time":125000,"text":"which will be available in the next few weeks,"},{"time":127000,"text":"you had every minute of your sleep displayed?"},{"time":130000,"text":"And this is, of course, as you can see, the awake is the orange."},{"time":133000,"text":"The REM sleep, rapid eye movement,"},{"time":135000,"text":"dream state, is in light green;"},{"time":137000,"text":"and light is gray, light sleep;"},{"time":139000,"text":"and deep sleep, the best restorative sleep,"},{"time":141000,"text":"is that dark green."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143000,"text":"How about counting every calorie?"},{"time":145000,"text":"And this is ability, in real time, to actually take"},{"time":148000,"text":"measurements of caloric intake"},{"time":150000,"text":"as well as expenditure, through a Band-Aid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153000,"text":"Now, what I've talked about are physiologic metrics."},{"time":156000,"text":"But what I want to get to, the next frontier,"},{"time":159000,"text":"very quickly, and why the stethoscope"},{"time":161000,"text":"is on its way out,"},{"time":163000,"text":"is because we can transcend listening to the valve sounds,"},{"time":167000,"text":"and the breath sounds, because now,"},{"time":169000,"text":"introduced by G.E. is a handheld ultra-sound."},{"time":172000,"text":"Why is this important? Because this is so much more sensitive."},{"time":175000,"text":"Here is an example of an abdominal ultrasound,"},{"time":178000,"text":"and also a cardiac echo, which can be sent wireless,"},{"time":182000,"text":"and then there's an example of fetal monitoring on your smartphone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186000,"text":"So, we're not just talking about physiologic metrics --"},{"time":189000,"text":"the key measurements of vital signs,"},{"time":192000,"text":"and all those things in physiology -- but also all the imaging"},{"time":195000,"text":"that one could look at in your smartphone."},{"time":197000,"text":"Now, this is an example of another obsolete technology,"},{"time":201000,"text":"soon to be buried: the Holter Monitor."},{"time":203000,"text":"Twenty-four hour recording, lots of wires."},{"time":205000,"text":"This is now a little tiny patch."},{"time":207000,"text":"You can put it on for two weeks"},{"time":209000,"text":"and send it in the mail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212000,"text":"Now, how does this work? Well,"},{"time":214000,"text":"there is these smart Band-Aids or these sensors"},{"time":216000,"text":"that one would put on, on a shoe or on the wrist."},{"time":219000,"text":"And this sends a signal"},{"time":222000,"text":"and it creates a body area network to a gateway."},{"time":226000,"text":"Gateway could be a smartphone or it could be a dedicated gateway,"},{"time":229000,"text":"as today many of these things are dedicated gateways,"},{"time":231000,"text":"because they are not so well integrated."},{"time":233000,"text":"That signal goes to the web, the cloud,"},{"time":236000,"text":"and then it can be processed and sent anywhere:"},{"time":238000,"text":"to a caregiver, to a physician,"},{"time":240000,"text":"back to the patient, etc."},{"time":242000,"text":"So, that's basically very simplistic technology"},{"time":245000,"text":"of how this works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247000,"text":"Now, I have this device on."},{"time":249000,"text":"I didn't want to take my shirt off to show you, but I can tell you it's on."},{"time":252000,"text":"This is a device that not only measures cardiac rhythm,"},{"time":256000,"text":"as you saw already,"},{"time":258000,"text":"but it also goes well beyond that."},{"time":261000,"text":"This is me now. And you can see the ECG."},{"time":264000,"text":"Below that's the actual heart rate and the trend;"},{"time":267000,"text":"to the right of that is a bioconductant."},{"time":269000,"text":"That's the fluid status,"},{"time":271000,"text":"fluid status, that's really important"},{"time":273000,"text":"if you're monitoring somebody with heart failure."},{"time":275000,"text":"And below that's temperature,"},{"time":277000,"text":"and respiration, and oxygen,"},{"time":279000,"text":"and then the position activity."},{"time":281000,"text":"So, this is really striking, because this device"},{"time":284000,"text":"measures seven things"},{"time":286000,"text":"that are very much vital signs"},{"time":289000,"text":"for monitoring someone with heart failure. OK?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":293000,"text":"And why is this important? Well,"},{"time":295000,"text":"this is the most expensive bed."},{"time":298000,"text":"What if we could reduce the need for hospital beds?"},{"time":301000,"text":"Well, we can. First of all, heart failure"},{"time":303000,"text":"is the number one reason"},{"time":306000,"text":"for hospital admissions and readmissions in this country."},{"time":309000,"text":"The cost of heart failure is 37 billion dollars a year,"},{"time":314000,"text":"which is 80 percent related to hospitalization."},{"time":317000,"text":"And in the course of 30 days after a hospital stay"},{"time":320000,"text":"for a Medicare greater than 65 years or older,"},{"time":323000,"text":"is -- 27 percent are readmitted in 30 days,"},{"time":326000,"text":"and by six months, over 56 percent are readmitted."},{"time":330000,"text":"So, can we improve that? Well the idea is"},{"time":332000,"text":"we take this device that I'm wearing,"},{"time":334000,"text":"and we put it on 600 patients with heart failure,"},{"time":338000,"text":"randomly assigned, versus 600 patients"},{"time":340000,"text":"who don't have active monitoring,"},{"time":342000,"text":"and see whether we can reduce heart failure readmissions,"},{"time":345000,"text":"and that's exciting. And we'll start that trial,"},{"time":347000,"text":"and you'll hear more about how we're going to do that,"},{"time":349000,"text":"but that's a type of wireless device trial"},{"time":352000,"text":"that could change medicine in the years ahead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355000,"text":"Why now? Why has this all of a sudden become"},{"time":358000,"text":"a reality, an exciting direction in the future of medicine?"},{"time":362000,"text":"What we have is, in a way, a perfect positive storm."},{"time":366000,"text":"This sets up consumer-driven healthcare."},{"time":368000,"text":"That's where this is all starting."},{"time":370000,"text":"Let me just give you specifics about why this is"},{"time":373000,"text":"a big movement if you're not aware of it:"},{"time":375000,"text":"1.2 million Americans"},{"time":377000,"text":"have gotten a Nike shoe, which is a body-area network"},{"time":380000,"text":"that connects the shoe, the sole of the shoe to the iPhone, or an iPod."},{"time":384000,"text":"And this Wired Magazine cover article"},{"time":386000,"text":"really captured a lot of this; it talked a lot about the Nike shoe"},{"time":389000,"text":"and how quickly that's been adopted to monitor exercise physiology"},{"time":392000,"text":"and energy expenditure."},{"time":394000,"text":"Here are some things, the principles"},{"time":396000,"text":"that are guiding principles to keep in mind:"},{"time":398000,"text":"\"A data-driven health revolution"},{"time":400000,"text":"promises to make us all"},{"time":402000,"text":"better, faster, and stronger. Living by numbers.\""},{"time":405000,"text":"And this one, which is really telling,"},{"time":407000,"text":"this was from July, this cover article:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":410000,"text":"\"The personal metrics movement goes way beyond"},{"time":413000,"text":"diet and exercise. It's about tracking every facet"},{"time":416000,"text":"of life, from sleep to mood to pain,"},{"time":418000,"text":"24/7/365.\""},{"time":421000,"text":"Well, I tried this device."},{"time":424000,"text":"A lot of you have gotten that Phillips Direct Life."},{"time":427000,"text":"I didn't have one of those,"},{"time":429000,"text":"but I got the Fitbit."},{"time":431000,"text":"That looks like this."},{"time":433000,"text":"It's like a wireless accelerometer, pedometer."},{"time":436000,"text":"And I want to just give you the results of that testing,"},{"time":438000,"text":"because I wanted to understand about the consumer movement."},{"time":441000,"text":"I hope the, by the way, the Phillips Direct Life works better --"},{"time":443000,"text":"I hope so."},{"time":445000,"text":"But this monitors food, it monitors activity and tracks weight."},{"time":449000,"text":"However you have to put in most of this stuff."},{"time":451000,"text":"The only thing it really tracks by itself is activity,"},{"time":454000,"text":"and even then, it's not complete."},{"time":456000,"text":"So, you exercise and it picks up the exercise."},{"time":459000,"text":"You put in your height and weight, it calculates BMI,"},{"time":462000,"text":"and of course it tells you how many calories you're expending"},{"time":465000,"text":"from the exercise, and how many you took in,"},{"time":468000,"text":"if you go in and enter all the foods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469000,"text":"But it really wants you to enter all your activity."},{"time":472000,"text":"And so I went to this,"},{"time":475000,"text":"and of course I was gratified that it picked up"},{"time":477000,"text":"the 42 minutes of exercise, elliptical exercise I did,"},{"time":481000,"text":"but then it wants more information."},{"time":483000,"text":"So, it says, \"You want to log sexual activity."},{"time":486000,"text":"How long did you do it for?\""},{"time":488000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":491000,"text":"And it says, \"How hard was it?\""},{"time":494000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":495000,"text":"Furthermore it says, \"Start time.\""},{"time":498000,"text":"Now, this doesn't appear -- this just doesn't work,"},{"time":500000,"text":"I mean, this just doesn't work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502000,"text":"So, now I want to move to sleep."},{"time":504000,"text":"Who would ever have thought you could have your own EEG"},{"time":507000,"text":"at your home, tagged to a very nice alarm clock, by the way?"},{"time":510000,"text":"This is the headband that goes with this alarm clock."},{"time":513000,"text":"It monitors your brainwaves continuously, when you're sleeping."},{"time":516000,"text":"So, I did this thing for seven days"},{"time":518000,"text":"getting ready for TEDMed."},{"time":520000,"text":"This is an important part of our life, one-third you're supposed to be sleeping."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523000,"text":"Of course how many here"},{"time":525000,"text":"have any problems with sleeping?"},{"time":529000,"text":"It's usually 90 percent. So, you tell me you sleep better than expected."},{"time":532000,"text":"Okay, well this was a week of"},{"time":535000,"text":"my life in sleeping,"},{"time":537000,"text":"and you get a Z.Q. score. Instead of an I.Q. score,"},{"time":540000,"text":"you get a Z.Q. score when you wake up."},{"time":542000,"text":"You say, \"Oh, OK.\" And a Z.Q. score"},{"time":544000,"text":"is adjusted to age,"},{"time":546000,"text":"and you want to get as high as you possibly can."},{"time":549000,"text":"So this is the moment-by-moment,"},{"time":551000,"text":"or minute-by-minute sleep."},{"time":553000,"text":"And you see that Z.Q. there was 80-odd."},{"time":556000,"text":"And the wake time is in orange."},{"time":559000,"text":"And this can be a problem, as I learned."},{"time":562000,"text":"Because it not only helps you with quantifying"},{"time":564000,"text":"your sleep,"},{"time":566000,"text":"but also tells others you're awake."},{"time":569000,"text":"So, when my wife came in and she"},{"time":572000,"text":"could tell you're awake."},{"time":574000,"text":"\"Eric, I want to talk. I want to talk.\""},{"time":576000,"text":"And I'm trying to play possum."},{"time":578000,"text":"This thing is very, very impressive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581000,"text":"OK. So, that's the first night."},{"time":584000,"text":"And this one is now 67,"},{"time":586000,"text":"and that's not a good score."},{"time":588000,"text":"And this tells you, of course, how much you had in REM sleep,"},{"time":590000,"text":"in deep sleep, and all this sort of thing."},{"time":592000,"text":"This was really fascinating because"},{"time":594000,"text":"this gave that quantitation"},{"time":596000,"text":"about all the different phases of sleep."},{"time":598000,"text":"So, it also then tells you how you do compared to your age group."},{"time":601000,"text":"It's like a managed competition of sleep."},{"time":604000,"text":"And really interesting stuff."},{"time":608000,"text":"Look at this thing and say, \"Well, I didn't think I was a very good sleeper,"},{"time":611000,"text":"but actually I did better than average in 50 to 60 year olds.\" OK?"},{"time":616000,"text":"And the key thing was, what I didn't know,"},{"time":618000,"text":"was that I was a really good dreamer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620000,"text":"OK. Now let's move from sleep to diseases."},{"time":625000,"text":"Eighty percent of Americans have chronic disease,"},{"time":628000,"text":"or 80 percent of age greater than 65 have"},{"time":631000,"text":"two or more chronic disease,"},{"time":633000,"text":"140 million Americans"},{"time":635000,"text":"have one or more chronic disease,"},{"time":637000,"text":"and 80 percent of our 1.5, whatever, trillion"},{"time":642000,"text":"expenditures are related to chronic disease."},{"time":644000,"text":"Now, diabetes is one of the big ones."},{"time":646000,"text":"Almost 24 million people have diabetes."},{"time":649000,"text":"And here is the latest map. It was published"},{"time":651000,"text":"just a little more than a week ago in the New York Times,"},{"time":654000,"text":"and it isn't looking good."},{"time":656000,"text":"That is, for men, 29 percent"},{"time":659000,"text":"in the country over 60 have Type II diabetes,"},{"time":662000,"text":"and women, although it's less, it's terribly high."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665000,"text":"But of course we have a way to measure that now"},{"time":667000,"text":"on a continuous basis,"},{"time":669000,"text":"with a sensor that detects blood glucose,"},{"time":671000,"text":"and it's important because we could detect"},{"time":673000,"text":"hyperglycemia that otherwise wouldn't be known,"},{"time":675000,"text":"and also hypoglycemia."},{"time":677000,"text":"And you can see the red dots, in this particular patient's case,"},{"time":680000,"text":"were finger sticks, which would have missed both ends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683000,"text":"But by continuous monitoring,"},{"time":685000,"text":"it captures all that vital information."},{"time":687000,"text":"The future of this though,"},{"time":689000,"text":"is being able to move this to a Band-Aid type phenomenon,"},{"time":691000,"text":"and that's not so far away."},{"time":694000,"text":"So, let me just give you, very quickly,"},{"time":696000,"text":"10 top targets for wireless medicine."},{"time":698000,"text":"All these things are possible --"},{"time":700000,"text":"some of them are very close,"},{"time":702000,"text":"or already, as you heard,"},{"time":704000,"text":"are available today, in some way or form."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706000,"text":"Alzheimer's disease:"},{"time":708000,"text":"there's five million people affected, and you can check"},{"time":710000,"text":"vital signs, activity, balance."},{"time":712000,"text":"Asthma: large number, we could detect things like"},{"time":715000,"text":"pollen count, air quality, respiratory rate. Breast cancer,"},{"time":718000,"text":"I'll show you an example of that real quickly."},{"time":721000,"text":"Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease."},{"time":724000,"text":"Depression, there's a great approach to that in mood disorders."},{"time":727000,"text":"Diabetes I've just mentioned. Heart failure we already talked about. Hypertension:"},{"time":730000,"text":"74 million people could have continuous blood-pressure monitoring"},{"time":733000,"text":"to come up with much better management and prevention."},{"time":738000,"text":"And obesity we already talked about, the ways to get to that."},{"time":741000,"text":"And sleep disorders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":743000,"text":"This is effective around the world. The access to smartphones"},{"time":746000,"text":"and cell phones today is extraordinary."},{"time":749000,"text":"And this article from The Economist summed it up beautifully"},{"time":752000,"text":"about the opportunities in health across the developing world:"},{"time":754000,"text":"\"Mobile phones made a bigger difference to the lives of more people,"},{"time":757000,"text":"more quickly, than any previous technology.\""},{"time":760000,"text":"And that's before we got going on the m-health world."},{"time":763000,"text":"Aging: The problem is enormous,"},{"time":766000,"text":"300,000 broken hips per year;"},{"time":768000,"text":"but the solutions are extraordinary,"},{"time":771000,"text":"and they include so many different things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":773000,"text":"One of the ones I just wanted to mention:"},{"time":775000,"text":"The iShoe is another example of a sensor that"},{"time":778000,"text":"improves proprioception among the elderly"},{"time":781000,"text":"to prevent falling."},{"time":782000,"text":"One of many different techniques using wireless sensors."},{"time":785000,"text":"So, we can change medicine across the continuum of care,"},{"time":788000,"text":"across the ages from premies or unborn children"},{"time":792000,"text":"to seniors; the pharmaceutical arena changes;"},{"time":795000,"text":"the full spectrum of disease -- I hope I've given you a sense of that --"},{"time":798000,"text":"across the globe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800000,"text":"There are two things that can really accelerate this whole process."},{"time":803000,"text":"One of them -- we're very fortunate -- is to develop a dedicated institute"},{"time":807000,"text":"and that's work that started with the work that Scripps with Qualcomm ..."},{"time":813000,"text":"and then the great fortune of meeting up with Gary and Mary West,"},{"time":816000,"text":"to get behind this wireless health institute."},{"time":819000,"text":"San Diego is an extraordinary place for this."},{"time":821000,"text":"There's over 650 wireless companies,"},{"time":824000,"text":"100 of which or more are working in wireless health."},{"time":827000,"text":"It's the number one source of commerce, and interestingly"},{"time":830000,"text":"it dovetails beautifully with over 500 life science companies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":833000,"text":"The wireless institute,"},{"time":836000,"text":"the West Wireless Health Institute,"},{"time":838000,"text":"is really the outgrowth of two extraordinary people"},{"time":842000,"text":"who are here this evening:"},{"time":844000,"text":"Gary and Mary West. And I'd like to give it up for them for getting behind this."},{"time":847000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":851000,"text":"Their fantastic philanthropic investment made this possible,"},{"time":854000,"text":"and this is really a nonprofit education center"},{"time":857000,"text":"which is just about to open. It looks like this,"},{"time":860000,"text":"this whole building dedicated."},{"time":863000,"text":"And what it's trying to do is accelerate this era:"},{"time":865000,"text":"to take unmet medical needs, to work and innovate --"},{"time":868000,"text":"and we just appointed the chief engineer, Mehran Mehregany,"},{"time":871000,"text":"it was announced on Monday --"},{"time":873000,"text":"then to move up with development,"},{"time":875000,"text":"clinical trial validation and then changing medical practice,"},{"time":878000,"text":"the most challenging thing of all,"},{"time":881000,"text":"requiring attention to reimbursement, healthcare policy, healthcare economics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":884000,"text":"The other big thing, besides having this fantastic"},{"time":887000,"text":"institute to catalyze this process"},{"time":890000,"text":"is guidance,"},{"time":893000,"text":"and that's of course relying on the fact that medicine goes digital."},{"time":896000,"text":"If we understand biology from genomics and omics"},{"time":900000,"text":"and wireless through physiologic phenotyping, that's big."},{"time":904000,"text":"Because what it does is allow a convergence like we've never had before."},{"time":907000,"text":"Over 80 major diseases have been cracked at the genomic level,"},{"time":912000,"text":"but this is quite extraordinary: More has been learned about"},{"time":915000,"text":"the underpinnings of disease in the last two and a half years"},{"time":917000,"text":"than in the history of man."},{"time":919000,"text":"And when you put that together with, for example,"},{"time":921000,"text":"now an app for the iPhone with your genotype"},{"time":924000,"text":"to guide drug therapy ..."},{"time":926000,"text":"but, the future -- we can now tell who's going to get Type II diabetes"},{"time":930000,"text":"from all the common variants,"},{"time":932000,"text":"and that's going to get filled in more"},{"time":934000,"text":"with low-frequency variants in the future."},{"time":936000,"text":"We can tell who's going to get breast cancer"},{"time":938000,"text":"from the various genes."},{"time":940000,"text":"We can also know who's likely to get atrial fibrillation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":943000,"text":"And finally, another example: sudden cardiac death."},{"time":946000,"text":"Each of these has a sensor."},{"time":948000,"text":"We can give glucose a sensor for diabetes to prevent it."},{"time":952000,"text":"We can prevent, or have the earliest detection possible,"},{"time":955000,"text":"for breast cancer with an ultrasound device"},{"time":958000,"text":"given to the patient."},{"time":960000,"text":"An iPatch, iRhythm, for atrial fibrillation."},{"time":963000,"text":"And vital-signs monitoring to prevent sudden cardiac death."},{"time":967000,"text":"We lose 700,000 people a year in the U.S. from sudden cardiac death."}]},{"cues":[{"time":970000,"text":"So, I hope I've convinced you of this,"},{"time":973000,"text":"of the impact on hospital clinic resources is profound"},{"time":977000,"text":"and then the impact on diseases is equally impressive"},{"time":980000,"text":"across all these different diseases and more."},{"time":983000,"text":"It's really taking individualized medicine to a new height"},{"time":987000,"text":"and it's hyper-innovative,"},{"time":990000,"text":"and I think it represents the black swan of medicine."},{"time":994000,"text":"Thanks for your attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":997000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}